&gt;&gt; scientist frames this as part of the scientific method, and expects a lot of
&gt;&gt; work to be done between the theory and the conclusions.  A believer often
&gt;&gt; starts with a theory,  and then states new things based on that.  The
&gt;&gt; scientist interprets the believer’s statements as the believers
&gt;&gt; ‘conclusions’, and is appalled at the lack of process that got the believer
&gt;&gt; from theory to conclusion.
