&gt;&gt; the believer understands the scientific method, and is making conclusions
&gt;&gt; from the scientific method, when the believer may really just be detailing
&gt;&gt; more theories.  The believer watches scientific-looking tv shows, uses
&gt;&gt; scientific-looking equipment, and uses scientific-sounding words like
&gt;&gt; ‘theory’ and ‘evidence’, without realizing this casts them into the
&gt;&gt; scientific method in the ears of the scientific community.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; What to do?  I think if the scientist/skeptic more often asked things like
&gt;&gt; “Are you sure of that, or is that a theory?”, and the paranormalist/
&gt;&gt; believer used the word ‘theory’ a lot more in their proclamations, it would
&gt;&gt; go a long way toward less hostilities.
